1)CREATE (ALREDY DONE)
++++++++++++++++++++++
USED TO CRATE TABLE
2)RENAME TABLE:
++++++++++++++++
RENAME TABLE is used to change the name of an existing table without affecting its data or structure.
SYNTAX:
ALTER TABLE TN
RENAME TO NEW NAME ;

EX:

ALTER TABLE EMP
RENAME TO EMPLOYEES;

SELECT * FROM EMPLOYEES;
3)ALTER:
++++++++
ALTER is used to modify the structure of an existing table.

I)TO ADD COLUMN:
---------------
SYNTAX:

ALTER TABLE TN
ADD COL_NAME DATA TYPE  [CONS];

EX:

ALTER TABLE EMPLOYEES
ADD CNO NUMBER(10) UNIQUE;

II)TO RENAME COLUMN:
--------------------
SYNTAX:

ALTER TABLE TN
RENAME COLUMN COL_NAME TO NEW_NAME;

ALTER TABLE EMPLOYEES
RENAME COLUMN CNO TO PHNO;

III)TO DROP COLUMN:

SYNTAX:
ALTER TABLE EMPLOYEES
DROP COLUMN COLUMN_NAME;

EX:

ALTER TABLE EMPLOYEES
DROP  COLUMN COL_NAME;


4)TO TRUNCATE TABLE:
+++++++++++++++++++
TRUNCATE is used to delete all rows from a table while keeping the table structure .
SYNTAX:

TRUNCATE TABLE TN;

EX:

TRUNCATE TABLE EMPLOYEES;


SELECT * 
FROM EMPLOYEES;(NO ROWS SELECTED)

TIME TRAVEL:
++++++++++++
Time Travel allows access to historical data of a table within a retention period(24 HRS), even after DELETE or TRUNCATE operations.

SYNTAX:

SELECT *
FROM EMPLOYEES AT(OFFSET=>-SECONDS);

EX:
SELECT *
FROM EMPLOYEES AT(OFFSET=>-SECONDS);

