2)DML:
++++++

I)INSERT
II)UPDATE
III)DELETE
IV)MERGE:

I) INSERT (ALREDY DONE):
INSERT is used to add new rows into a table.

II)UPDATE:
UPDATE is used to modify existing data in a table based on a condition.

SYNTAX:
UPDATE TN
SET CPLNAME1 =VALUE,COLNAME2=VALUE,,,,,,N
WHERE <FILTER CONDITION>;

EX:


UPDATE EMPLOYEES
SET SAL=10000
WHERE EID=101;

III)DELETE:
DELETE is used to remove specific rows from a table based on a condition.
SYNTAX:
DELETE FROM TN
WHERE <FILTER CONDITION>;

EX:

DELETE FROM EMPLOYEES WHERE EID=106;















